  "notes": [
    {
      "text": {
        "ja": "**ポモドーロ・テクニック**: **25分**集中 → 5分休憩を1コマとし、4コマごとに15〜30分の長い休憩を取る。集中力を維持しやすい",
        "en": "**Pomodoro Technique**: **25 min** focus → 5 min break = 1 session. Take a 15–30 min break every 4 sessions to maintain concentration"
      },
      "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pomodoro_Technique"
    },
    {
      "text": {
        "ja": "**間隔反復**（スペースドリピティション）: 忘れかけた頃に復習すると記憶が定着しやすい\n- 1日後 → 3日後 → 1週間後 → 1ヶ月後",
        "en": "**Spaced repetition**: review material just as you're about to forget it\n- 1 day → 3 days → 1 week → 1 month"
      },
      "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spaced_repetition"
    },
    {
      "text": {
        "ja": "**アクティブリコール**: 教科書を読み返すだけでなく、自分でテストを作って答える方が記憶に残る。「思い出す」行為自体が学習",
        "en": "**Active recall**: testing yourself is more effective than re-reading. The act of retrieving information strengthens memory"
      },
      "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Active_recall"
    },
    {
      "text": {
        "ja": "**インターリーブ学習**: 同じ科目を長時間やるより、複数科目を交互に勉強する方が長期記憶に効果的",
        "en": "**Interleaving**: alternating between different subjects is more effective for long-term retention than studying one subject for hours"
      },
      "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interleaving_(psychology)"
    },
    {
      "text": {
        "ja": "**過去問は最強の教材**。出題傾向の把握、時間配分の練習、弱点の発見が同時にできる。テスト**2週間前**から着手が理想",
        "en": "**Past exams are the most effective study material** — they reveal question patterns, help practice time management, and identify weaknesses. Start **2 weeks** before the test"
      }
    },
    {
      "text": {
        "ja": "苦手科目は**1日の最初**に取り組む。脳が疲れていない朝のうちに難しい科目をやり、得意科目は午後に回す",
        "en": "Tackle weak subjects **first thing in the day** when your brain is fresh. Save stronger subjects for the afternoon"
      }
    },
    {
      "text": {
        "ja": "ノートまとめは「書く」こと自体が目的ではない。自分の言葉で**要約・構造化**し、後から見返せる形にすることが重要",
        "en": "Note-taking isn't about writing things down — it's about **summarizing and structuring** information in your own words for later review"
      }
    },
    {
      "text": {
        "ja": "睡眠は記憶の定着に不可欠。徹夜での詰め込みは非効率。**6時間以上**の睡眠を確保して翌日に復習する方が効果的",
        "en": "Sleep is essential for memory consolidation. All-night cramming is inefficient — get **6+ hours** of sleep and review the next day"
      }
    },
    {
      "text": {
        "ja": "1コマ ≈ **25分**（ポモドーロ1回分）を想定。自分のペースに合わせて、1コマの長さや各科目の目標を調整してください",
        "en": "1 session ≈ **25 minutes** (one Pomodoro). Adjust session length and per-subject goals to match your pace"
      }
    },
    {
      "text": {
        "ja": "勉強の「量」を可視化することでモチベーションが維持しやすくなる。カウンターが増えていく達成感を活用しよう",
        "en": "Visualizing study volume helps maintain motivation. Use the satisfaction of watching your counters grow to stay on track"
      }
    }
  ]
}
